         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0134">
               <p>A corporal in the Life Guards, Bell converted in <placeName>London</placeName>
                  about <date when="1758">1758</date>. The noisy prayer meetings over which he
                  officiated in <date when="1761">1761</date> excited Methodists all over
                     <placeName>England</placeName>. He increasingly claimed unique spiritual
                  privileges, the power to heal miraculously, and predicted that the world would end
                  on <date when="1763-02-28">Feb. 28, 1763</date>. When <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> resisted these claims, Bell
                  withdrew from Methodism, never to return. See <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 80; and
                  Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 26.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
